org.anchoranalysis.plugin.operator.feature.bean.conditional

Class IfCondition<T extends FeatureInput>

  • Object
    • AnchorBean<B>

            • FeatureUnaryGeneric<T>
              • IfCondition<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - feature input-type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParamsInitializer<FeatureInitParams>

    public class IfCondition<T extends FeatureInput>
extends FeatureUnaryGeneric<T>
    The result of featureCondition is compared to a threshold, and then either the underlying feature is calculated (positive case), or featureElse is (negative case)

    The positive case is when relation(featureCondition,value) is true..

    Author:
    Owen Feehan
